{
  "doc_id": "35470",
  "text": "The PmrA-activated pbgPE operon [also referred to as arn [CITATION_1] and pmrF [CITATION_2] ] consists of seven genes. The first five genes encode proteins that participate in the biosynthesis and incorporation of 4-aminoarabinose into lipid A [CITATION_3] ), but are not required for resistance to Fe(III) . On the other hand, strains with in-frame deletions in either of the last two genes of the pbgPE operon (designated pbgE2 and pbgE3) could not grow in the presence of 100 mM Fe(III) . They differed instead in their resistance to polymyxin B: a pbgE2 mutant was hypersensitive to polymyxin B whereas a pbgE3 mutant was not [CITATION_4] . The biochemical function of the PbgE2 and PbgE3 proteins remains unknown. The PmrA-activated yibD and dgoA genes are dispensable for resistance to polymyxin B and Fe(III) [CITATION_5] .",
